gomodel:SYNGO_1188  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099056 replaced by GO:0042734" , "Rationale: Presynaptic localisation of Glycine alpha 3 subunit, based on reduced facilitation by forskolin of mIPSC-frequency in GLRA3 KO mice.\n\n8/9/2017 Pim\n- Important to note here is that the basal glycinergic transmission (amplitude) in not negatively affected in KO animals. There are even larger mIPSC-amplitude in Glra3 -/- mice at P15-21. This shows that the GLRA3 is not present in the postsynapse mediating the postsynaptic currents. In contrast, forscolin is shown affect IPSC freq (increased SV release) via GLRA3.\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen. Experimental description: p.2: GlyRa3-deficient mice (Harvey et al., 2004) were obtained from a colony that was crossbred with a transgenic line (GlyT2-EGFP) that expresses the Green fluorescent protein (EGFP) under the control of the glycine transporter 2 (GlyT2) (Zeilhofer et al., 2005). Homozygous GlyRa3-deficient mice that express EGFP are fertile. They were maintained as homozygous breeding pairs (Glra3 /) and served as experimental animals. In all experiments, GlyT2-EGFP (Glra3 +/+) mice served as controls. -- Highlighted 07 Aug 2017" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9425-2935" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1188" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

